1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:01,896
(Previously)
Raffy called. He said it's urgent.

2
00:00:01,920 --> 00:00:03,480
I want to drop out of the play.

3
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:06,640
When you talked to Raffy the other day,
is that really all he said?

4
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:07,800
Why?

5
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,056
What do you think he said to me?

6
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:10,800
There's no way we're ever breaking up.

7
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,080
How dare you ask me
to be your boyfriend after that?

8
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:16,040
I swear, nothing happened.

9
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:19,640
From now on, I don't have a shitty friend
and a shitty boyfriend like you two.

10
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,840
It was you, wasn't it?

11
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:21,960
I didn't do it.

12
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:24,960
Can I stay here with you?

13
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:26,520
If I let you in again…

14
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,200
I'm a damn idiot.

15
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:30,760
Dean.

16
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:32,480
Gameplay.

17
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,200
It's okay, Dean.

18
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:35,800
I'm right here.

19
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,600
(Episode 10: The Show Must Go On)

20
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Tua.

21
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:50,920
Tua, come out and talk to me.

22
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:58,560
Tua!

23
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:00,560
Tua, come out and talk to me.

24
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,400
Tua.

25
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:04,480
Tua, I know you're in there.

26
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,680
Come out and talk, please.

27
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:12,440
Are you here for Dean?

28
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,880
Go look somewhere else. I kicked him out.

29
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:16,160
I'm not here for Dean.

30
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,560
I'm here for you.

31
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,680
Will you let me in, please?

32
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,120
No.

33
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:22,680
Just leave.

34
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:26,000
Tua, I called you so many times,
but you didn't pick up.

35
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,040
Then stop calling.

36
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:30,360
I'm sorry.

37
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:34,000
Tua, will you give me a chance to explain?

38
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,880
I'll prove myself however you want.

39
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,160
I don't want anything from you.

40
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:43,400
Don't do shit for me,
and don't try to prove anything.

41
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,920
Just leave.

42
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,896
Did you spend the night here, Boston?

43
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,400
Whether he did or not
is none of your damn business.

44
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:12,360
Don't tell me you think we're still together.

45
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,560
Just go. I don't want to see your face.

46
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,700
"Only Friends : Dream On"

47
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,080
Excuse me. One more.

48
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,200
Hey. One more.

49
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,200
What the hell?

50
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,440
What do you want?

51
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,720
Hey. I'm sorry.

52
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,840
My friend's wasted.

53
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,880
Please, I'm begging you.

54
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,400
I'm sorry on his behalf.

55
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,840
Jack, are you okay?

56
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,080
That's enough. You're coming with me.

57
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,880
Jeez.

58
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,680
Are you alright?

59
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,280
Your car's right here.

60
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:56,720
Careful.

61
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,520
Why?

62
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:55,440
Don't you always want me?

63
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,120
Here I am.

64
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,640
I don't think we should, Jack.

65
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:54,760
Oh, you're awake.

66
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:58,240
Just in time. I made breakfast.

67
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:01,000
Want coffee too?

68
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,640
Please.

69
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,760
Are you ready to tell me?

70
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,920
Do you remember Jack?

71
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,480
My boyfriend.

72
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,040
Of course I do.

73
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:38,080
The one who barged into my party
and split my brow open with a punch.

74
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:43,240
The reason you quit hosting.

75
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:53,000
He caught me working behind his back.

76
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,800
That's why he lost it.

77
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,400
But you already quit.

78
00:07:58,920 --> 00:07:59,960
What happened this time?

79
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,920
I got drunk.

80
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,400
And… I almost kissed my co-performer.

81
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:24,760
Worse, he's my housemate's boyfriend.

82
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:30,720
So I got kicked out.

83
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:35,320
But we didn't cross the line.

84
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,440
Did you explain that to him?

85
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,560
I did.

86
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,240
No one believed me.

87
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:52,960
You know that when I commit,
I don't do things like that.

88
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,080
I can't…

89
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,680
If I don't feel anything for them.

90
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,080
Make yourself comfortable.

91
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:11,440
You know you're always welcome here.

92
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,440
Eat something first.

93
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,080
Yes.

94
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,440
Hey. You're awake?

95
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,040
Here. I made this for you.

96
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,640
I found a bag of matcha in the kitchen.

97
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,160
Thought I'd make you a drink.

98
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,160
Thank you so much.

99
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,920
Did you crash here last night?

100
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,480
You don't remember anything?

101
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,520
So…

102
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:39,560
Last night,
you and I…

103
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:45,880
I should book a ride home.

104
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,040
I'll see you at uni.

105
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,480
Raffy.

106
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,880
Do you want to go to uni together?

107
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,720
Ho. Ho. Ho.

108
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,200
Ho. Ho. Ho.

109
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,560
Ho. Ho. Ho.

110
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,240
Let me do a quick soundcheck.

111
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,360
Up a bit.

112
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:27,560
A bit more.

113
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:29,960
A bit more.

114
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,080
Yeah, that's about right.

115
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,600
Hi, Jack.

116
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,840
Did you meet Raffy outside
and walk in together?

117
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:08,960
We're in the same production.

118
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,800
It makes sense you'd get close, right?

119
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,360
We came together.

120
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:20,320
Who knows? After the play,
Raffy and I might get together.

121
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,000
Do you think
Jack and Raffy will actually go out?

122
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:43,520
I think so.

123
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:46,360
I think Raffy leaked the video
and caused the breakup.

124
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:48,200
That's horrible.

125
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,200
Right.

126
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,920
Do you need a hand?

127
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,280
No, it's okay. We've got it.

128
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,440
So what are you going to do?

129
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:21,920
About what?

130
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,960
Are you getting together with him?

131
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,160
Not answering.

132
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:30,800
Okay.

133
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,600
I got my answer.

134
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,600
What's with you?

135
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,120
You got what you wanted, huh?

136
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,680
You've been waiting for this moment.

137
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,040
Congratulations.

138
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:44,480
For what exactly?

139
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:46,120
Don't start it.

140
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,440
I don't want to fight you.

141
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:52,480
I know we're not a thing.

142
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:56,720
But can I give you a warning, as a friend?

143
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:00,800
I wouldn't get with Jack.

144
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:06,640
You know he's only doing this to hurt Dean.

145
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:15,880
So?

146
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:21,360
I'm not dating anyone right now,
and Jack needs me.

147
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,320
I have the right.

148
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,720
Can we talk?

149
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,120
About what?

150
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:51,920
Why are you doing this?

151
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,200
Are you getting with Raffy just to hurt me?

152
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:55,840
It doesn't seem like you.

153
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,160
Then what does?

154
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,760
Why?

155
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,800
I just want something new.

156
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,360
I'm sorry.

157
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:07,560
Can't you give me one more chance?

158
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:11,000
I promise I won't mess up like that again.

159
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,400
Dean, listen to me.

160
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,200
I have nothing left to trust you with.

161
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:20,920
If I'm giving anyone a chance,
I might as well give it to someone else.

162
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:24,800
At least they'd get to hurt me only once.

163
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,120
Hey, Dean.

164
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:32,920
There you are. I've been looking for you.

165
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:39,880
What's up?

166
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:42,000
What brings you here?

167
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,480
It's still early.

168
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,240
I know.

169
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:48,400
I just dropped by to bring you some snacks.

170
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:49,720
Eat. You'll need the energy.

171
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,640
Thank you so much.

172
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:55,280
And these flowers are for you, Dean.

173
00:15:58,960 --> 00:15:59,960
Thank you.

174
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,160
You shouldn't have.

175
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,600
I want to.

176
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,800
I thought it might help
soften your heart a little.

177
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,640
It's your first show today, right?

178
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,960
Bet you're all nervous.

179
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,080
My actors aren't nervous.

180
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:19,440
They're professionals.

181
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,760
Alright, everyone. Let's get ready.

182
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:25,760
We're about to…

183
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:28,640
Hey.

184
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:31,560
Gameplay brought snacks for the crew.

185
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:33,040
Oh.

186
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:34,800
Thank you.

187
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,600
I'll hand them out.

188
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:40,360
If you're done here, please leave.

189
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,480
No outsiders allowed.

190
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,600
Staff only.

191
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,800
Jack, be nice.

192
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:46,960
It's fine.

193
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:50,800
I'll wait for the doors to open.

194
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:56,160
Do your best, Dean.

195
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,440
I'm rooting for you.

196
00:16:58,760 --> 00:16:59,760
Sure.

197
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,536
I'm heading in. You should too.

198
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:09,080
Come on. Get ready. Stand by.

199
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,440
Do you practice here often?

200
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,240
I haven't seen you before.

201
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,280
Not really.

202
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,520
I only come when I have free time.

203
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,760
When's your next free time?

204
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,000
I'd like a rematch.

205
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,880
Hey. You done, man?

206
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:15,680
Let's go.

207
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,160
I've got to go.

208
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,800
Can we exchange contacts?

209
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:30,000
Let's just say if you're lucky, we'll meet again.

210
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,360
My name is Romeo.

211
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,680
My name is Romeo too.

212
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:19,240
Tua.

213
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:21,000
What's going on with you and Boston?

214
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,320
Are you talking to him again?

215
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,400
That's my business.

216
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:25,640
None of your concern.

217
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,200
Of course it concerns me.

218
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,600
We haven't settled things yet.

219
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,080
Yeah. I'm seeing Boston.

220
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,600
You're seeing him?

221
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,400
Got a problem with that?

222
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,320
I'm done putting in effort for people.

223
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,800
I want to give a chance to
someone who puts in effort for me.

224
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:47,040
Arnold, get ready for the next scene.

225
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:55,640
Hurry up.

226
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:58,920
Your Romeo's waiting.

227
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:03,880
Come on.

228
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:04,920
Okay.

229
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:26,720
Can I talk to you?

230
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,000
If it's about the play,
stick to what we rehearsed.

231
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:41,040
If it's personal, don't.

232
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,576
I'm not listening to your made-up stories.

233
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,920
Will you drop the attitude?

234
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,960
I'm going to get the actor now.

235
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:56,760
About Gameplay, it's not what you think.

236
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,520
I had nowhere else to go, so I—

237
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:00,880
Ran back to your safe little nest.

238
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,120
Gosh.

239
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:05,920
Someone like you.

240
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:09,680
What about someone like me?

241
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,200
You're a predictable character.

242
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,000
And you're not?

243
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:19,760
I can tell you're using Raffy
to get back at me.

244
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:21,120
Right?

245
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:24,840
Dean, get over yourself.

246
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,200
I just chose to love someone who loves me.

247
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:31,560
Love?

248
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,360
Do you really love him, Jack?

249
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:36,000
Do you? Answer me.

250
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,200
Answer me!

251
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:41,160
See? You can't.

252
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:43,520
Because you don't love him, Jack.

253
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:46,320
You picked him as my replacement
just to hurt my feelings, didn't you?

254
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,320
Yes!

255
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:51,680
Raffy is your replacement.

256
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:53,600
Anyone can be replaced.

257
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:58,720
One day, he'll be number one.

258
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:01,200
Both on stage and in my heart.

259
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,760
He's here.

260
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,680
The actor is ready. I'm bringing him there.

261
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:42,880
Ready?

262
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:46,080
Five, four, three, two, one.

263
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:07,040
Aren't you afraid,
coming to see me in this kind of place?

264
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:12,360
If we love each other,
what's there to be afraid of?

265
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:19,400
You should go back
before someone sees us.

266
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:36,480
I want to stay with you tonight.

267
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:39,640
Can I?

268
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,520
We'll take a 15-minute intermission.

269
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,000
Where's Raffy?

270
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,400
Wasn't that his line?

271
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:42,680
I have no clue where he went.

272
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,600
What's wrong?

273
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:31,800
Nothing.

274
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:34,000
Nothing, but you're crying?

275
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,120
Hey.

276
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:42,560
Don't go anywhere.

277
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,120
I just came to keep you company.

278
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,960
You can let it out with me.

279
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,640
I don't have tissues, though.

280
00:26:00,560 --> 00:26:02,920
Just my sleeves. You can use them.

281
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:18,800
I'm such an idiot.

282
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:23,440
I was stupid not to believe you.

283
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,600
Hey.

284
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:27,360
Easy.

285
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:29,840
What happened?

286
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:35,560
I heard Jack and Dean.

287
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:44,680
To Jack…

288
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:50,760
I'm just Dean's replacement.

289
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:58,480
I was stupid to think I ever had a chance.

290
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,160
Yell at me.

291
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,360
I said yell at me.

292
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:12,040
Go on. Rub it in my face.

293
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:24,840
You're not stupid at all.

294
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:29,880
No one is, not about something like this.

295
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,240
Why?

296
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:42,240
Why did this happen to me?

297
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,840
Don't think like that, Raffy.

298
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:51,800
You shouldn't have to feel this way at all.

299
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,240
Boston.

300
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,360
I need to talk to you about Tua.

301
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,040
I've got nothing to say to you.

302
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:26,520
It'll only take a minute.

303
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,640
Are you serious about Tua?

304
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:35,000
He's not just a fling to you, is he?

305
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:36,120
What are you talking about?

306
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:39,880
I asked if you're serious about Tua.

307
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,320
I'm warning you.

308
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:46,800
If you make him miserable,
you answer to me.

309
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:51,280
If you don't want him miserable,
why don't you take care of him yourself?

310
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:55,160
And honestly,
do you even have the right to say that?

311
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:05,120
Tua and I aren't together.

312
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,320
What do you mean?

313
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:14,040
Exactly what I said. We're not dating.

314
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,040
But you stayed at his place that night.

315
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:17,920
I was just keeping him company.

316
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,320
My friend was devastated.

317
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:22,160
Would you have left him alone?

318
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:27,000
I did want Tua.

319
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,520
But I know now isn't my time.

320
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:34,280
But if you're too late, maybe it will be.

321
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,240
You can see how much he loves you.

322
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:48,600
Otherwise, he wouldn't be that broken.

323
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:53,560
That's all I have to say.

324
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:03,160
Alright. We're moving into Act Two.

325
00:30:03,320 --> 00:30:05,480
- Everyone, no mistakes.
- Okay.

326
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,560
Stick to the rehearsal.

327
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:07,080
Got it?

328
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:08,720
Yeah.

329
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:09,760
As for this part…

330
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:11,600
Hey!

331
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,320
You're such a fucking asshole.

332
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:18,800
You've got a problem with Dean.

333
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,480
Why drag someone else into it?

334
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:22,080
How could you do that to Raffy?

335
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:24,600
How could you
make him a stand-in for Dean?

336
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:26,216
And how the hell is that your problem?

337
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,640
Raffy himself hasn't said anything.

338
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,256
Just because you don't see it
doesn't mean he's not hurting.

339
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:34,080
Ruin your life all you want.

340
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:35,560
Don't drag anyone else down with you.

341
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:37,720
Fuck you!

342
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,600
Jack, stop!

343
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:41,520
Stop it, assholes!
That's enough!

344
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,720
Knock it off!

345
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:46,520
Save it till after the show.

346
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:51,640
I've got more than
enough to deal with already.

347
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:55,520
Just maintain your duty. Is that so hard?

348
00:30:58,560 --> 00:30:59,560
Out.

349
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:01,320
Act Two is about to start.

350
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:02,840
Go get ready.

351
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:05,360
Move!

352
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:25,480
I never thought we'd have this day.

353
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:38,120
Do you remember what I told you?

354
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:50,800
If anyone tried to stand between us, I'd fight.

355
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,640
And do you remember what I asked you?

356
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,880
If it were you…

357
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:06,160
would you fight for us?

358
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:09,880
You said if you couldn't win the fight,

359
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:13,360
you'd take my hand and run.

360
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:19,040
I want to run away with you.

361
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:23,840
I want to start over.

362
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,920
I want to set things right with you.

363
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:32,640
That's not the script.

364
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,720
Is Dean improvising?

365
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:51,960
I love you.

366
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:53,960
And I believe…

367
00:32:56,720 --> 00:33:02,120
that if we still love each other,
we'll get to be together.

368
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,440
I love you too.

369
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:13,000
And I'll stay with you forever, Romeo.

370
00:34:57,040 --> 00:35:03,040
That ending scene on stage,
I meant those words for you, Jack.

371
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:08,720
Do you remember what we talked about?

372
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:14,120
Back when we were reinterpreting this play.

373
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,480
I don't like it when actors go off script.

374
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:22,560
Jack.

375
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:27,640
Can we go back the way we were?

376
00:35:31,240 --> 00:35:32,240
Can we not do this?

377
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,120
This is how we were.

378
00:35:38,760 --> 00:35:41,320
You running back to Gameplay,
just like before.

379
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:58,480
I think I'm too naïve
to let Romeo and Romeo end up together.

380
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:07,120
Actually, tearing them apart by death
is the best solution.

381
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:23,840
Well?

382
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:25,240
Are you coming with me?

383
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:29,240
Give me a sec. I need to tidy up first.

384
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,320
Mm.

385
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:32,800
Raffy.

386
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:42,880
Rome.

387
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,440
Can I talk to Jack for a minute?

388
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:48,880
Do whatever you want.

389
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,400
Your life, your choice.

390
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:54,160
Will you wait for me out front?

391
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:56,880
No.

392
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:58,400
I'm leaving.

393
00:36:58,960 --> 00:36:59,960
I'm done waiting.

394
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:08,920
Are you coming with me?

395
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:12,600
I'll take you home.

396
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:17,320
It's okay.

397
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:29,400
I'm sorry you had to hear
what I said to Dean.

398
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:36,320
You really mean that?

399
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:44,560
Do you actually
want me to be his replacement?

400
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:56,480
Jack.

401
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,200
Don't do this.

402
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:13,720
Don't try to beat him
by dragging me into it and hurting me too.

403
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:27,080
I'm sorry.

404
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:38,720
I get you.

405
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,880
Wanting to win, I feel that too.

406
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:48,200
I've always wanted to beat Dean.

407
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:52,120
That's why I did everything I did.

408
00:38:56,240 --> 00:38:57,680
I don't know if you'll believe this,

409
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:04,920
but that night, when Dean was with Arnold,
I did film them.

410
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:08,160
I was going to show you the video.

411
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:10,880
But I didn't.

412
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:14,000
It's not that I didn't want to.

413
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,080
I really fucking did.

414
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:22,320
But maybe it's for the best.

415
00:39:25,040 --> 00:39:29,840
Because in the end,
I can't be anyone's replacement.

416
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:34,160
I like you, Jack.

417
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:40,160
But I don't think I love you.

418
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:00,600
I meant what I said.

419
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,880
We should love someone who truly loves us.

420
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:10,560
Tua, are you staying late?

421
00:40:10,560 --> 00:40:12,280
Everyone else in the theater is gone.

422
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:14,880
I'm going to pack my things first.

423
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:15,080
Okay.

424
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,880
Can you turn off the lights on your way out?

425
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:19,200
Mm, sure.

426
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:20,000
See you.

427
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,560
Okay. See you. Bye.

428
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:38,680
Tua.

429
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:44,640
I know you and Boston aren't together.

430
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:51,200
So?

431
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:57,720
I don't know if you're doing this to hurt me

432
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:59,800
or if you really
don't want me in your life anymore.

433
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,080
But I don't care.

434
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:03,960
I just came to tell you one last time.

435
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:06,400
Dean and I didn't cross the line.

436
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,240
What I felt for Dean was only for the play.

437
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:18,000
The only person
I have real feelings for is you, Tua.

438
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:31,880
Do you know how heartbroken I am?

439
00:41:32,040 --> 00:41:33,040
Of course I do.

440
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:35,800
I understand everything.

441
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:40,160
But I'm begging you.

442
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:43,320
Please give me a chance.

443
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:45,160
Please.

444
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:54,000
Tua, I love you.

445
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:59,200
And I know you love me too.

446
00:41:59,640 --> 00:42:00,320
Right, Tua?

447
00:42:00,520 --> 00:42:01,960
That's enough, Arnold.

448
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:03,280
Just tell me.

449
00:42:06,240 --> 00:42:07,240
Let go.

450
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,640
I'm not letting you go until I get an answer.

451
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:11,240
Say you don't love me.

452
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,400
Stop it, Arnold.

453
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:13,400
Let go of me.
No.

454
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,000
Say it.

455
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:19,440
Say you don't love me anymore.

456
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:20,880
Say it, Tua.
Let go.

457
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:22,200
No.

458
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,760
Not until you say you don't love me anymore.

459
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:26,640
Say it, Tua. Say you don't love me anymore.

460
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:27,400
Say it.
Say it now.

461
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:29,960
Say you don't love me.

462
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:30,960
Let go.

463
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:32,000
Say it.

464
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:32,640
Do it!
Now!

465
00:42:33,600 --> 00:42:34,600
Yes!

466
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:38,920
I love you.

467
00:43:44,760 --> 00:43:47,240
I miss the times
when we were together like this.

468
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:50,480
Do you know, Tua?

469
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:58,320
Living my life without you…
I really can't imagine that.

470
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:04,520
Thank you for giving me a chance.

471
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:11,560
Honestly,

472
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:17,840
I don't even know if
what I did counts as giving you one.

473
00:44:20,520 --> 00:44:22,600
Part of me wants to stay like this,

474
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:28,160
but part of me is still hurting.

475
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:31,720
I'm just… confused.

476
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:39,560
I'm sorry.

477
00:44:41,680 --> 00:44:43,160
Sorry for making you feel this way.

478
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:47,520
Stop apologizing.

479
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:52,120
I just need time.

480
00:44:55,320 --> 00:44:57,400
Then take all the time you need, Tua.

481
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:02,160
But let me stay by your side

482
00:45:03,600 --> 00:45:05,080
and take care of you…

483
00:45:07,120 --> 00:45:08,120
like this.

484
00:45:09,440 --> 00:45:10,440
Please.

485
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,120
I don't know.

486
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:20,160
It's the first time I've ever felt like this.

487
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:38,680
I think I need time to really think it through.

488
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:50,160
If that's what you want, then it's fine.

489
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:59,600
I'll do my best to win you back.

490
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:04,440
To make you smile again.

491
00:46:27,400 --> 00:46:28,400
Why are you here?

492
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:30,920
I thought I'd leave with you.

493
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:34,360
But you were sulking and left first,
so I had to follow you here.

494
00:46:45,840 --> 00:46:48,240
You're always the one right by my side.

495
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:54,520
Thank you.

496
00:46:55,720 --> 00:46:57,560
Thank you for getting yourself hurt for me.

497
00:47:05,480 --> 00:47:06,960
You don't have to thank me.

498
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:09,720
Jack's a real asshole.

499
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:12,040
No one deserves what you went through.

500
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:15,640
What a damn hero.

501
00:47:17,560 --> 00:47:18,640
So what now?

502
00:47:19,520 --> 00:47:20,920
You going back to Jack?

503
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:23,160
If so, then all of this was for nothing.

504
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:26,360
I don't think so.

505
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:32,200
I think I'll open up to someone new.

506
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:35,160
Or maybe…

507
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:40,880
someone who's
actually willing to wait for me.

508
00:47:48,160 --> 00:47:49,800
I don't know.

509
00:47:51,760 --> 00:47:52,760
It's just…

510
00:47:56,880 --> 00:47:59,720
As you know, I've been hurt over and over.

511
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:04,040
Now I don't know if
I can stand by and wait for you anymore.

512
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:14,120
I'm sorry…

513
00:48:17,160 --> 00:48:18,880
for hurting you again and again.

514
00:48:25,920 --> 00:48:27,320
I accept your apology.

515
00:48:30,080 --> 00:48:32,240
But my feelings are already broken.

516
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:35,520
They need time to heal.

517
00:48:49,200 --> 00:48:50,200
I understand.

518
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:57,840
From now on, I'll be the one chasing you.

519
00:49:00,880 --> 00:49:02,800
I'll make you fall for me all over again.

520
00:49:07,080 --> 00:49:08,080
Okay.

521
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:09,320
You can try.

522
00:49:20,880 --> 00:49:24,840
As I said, I won't stand by
as anyone's substitute anymore.

523
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:30,040
Are you okay, Jack?

524
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:32,096
You're not mad at me, are you?

525
00:49:32,120 --> 00:49:33,560
For calling you out during the play?

526
00:49:35,320 --> 00:49:36,600
How could I be?

527
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:42,920
I should be thanking you
for snapping me back to my senses.

528
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:46,240
Otherwise, the play
would've been an even bigger mess.

529
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:48,760
But I'll give it to you, Jack.

530
00:49:49,520 --> 00:49:51,720
You broke up with Dean,
and you can still work with him.

531
00:49:52,320 --> 00:49:54,000
I heard you even had to see him every day.

532
00:49:58,720 --> 00:49:59,840
Actually, I think I'm wrong.

533
00:50:00,240 --> 00:50:01,320
I don't think he can.

534
00:50:05,240 --> 00:50:06,360
I don't know.

535
00:50:07,560 --> 00:50:09,960
I'm always telling people to

536
00:50:09,960 --> 00:50:11,800
separate work from personal stuff,

537
00:50:12,520 --> 00:50:14,880
but now I'm the one who can't.

538
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:19,000
Come on.

539
00:50:19,760 --> 00:50:21,280
At least you realize it.

540
00:50:21,880 --> 00:50:25,480
You and Dean are both my best friends.

541
00:50:26,240 --> 00:50:30,320
I'll be honest, I don't
want you two breaking up at all.

542
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:32,400
What a damn headache.

543
00:50:33,520 --> 00:50:39,960
Anyway, thank you both
for keeping me company tonight.

544
00:50:42,120 --> 00:50:43,840
I didn't want to spiral alone in my room.

545
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:49,840
Boston, thanks so much

546
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:52,120
for helping with the play.

547
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:54,280
Don't mention it.

548
00:50:54,960 --> 00:50:56,320
Your project was fun.

549
00:50:58,200 --> 00:50:59,800
Alright, alright.

550
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:03,480
Enough drama. Just drink.

551
00:51:03,480 --> 00:51:04,600
Cheers!

552
00:51:10,400 --> 00:51:12,440
I said stop being sad.

553
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:37,920
Excuse me.

554
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:39,440
You ended up in my photos.

555
00:51:39,920 --> 00:51:41,120
How should I send them to you?

556
00:51:43,080 --> 00:51:44,920
Is that your subtle way of getting my contact?

557
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:49,720
I'm Boston. What's your name?

558
00:51:51,880 --> 00:51:52,880
I'm Win.

559
00:51:55,520 --> 00:51:56,520
Did you come alone?

560
00:51:58,280 --> 00:51:59,280
I did.

561
00:52:01,120 --> 00:52:02,240
But my partner's on the way.

562
00:52:04,080 --> 00:52:08,720
Then until they get here, we can hang out.

563
00:52:12,280 --> 00:52:13,280
Win.

564
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:37,120
How have you been?

565
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:41,280
Good.

566
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:47,600
It's been so long, and you're still the same.

567
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,000
Yeah?

568
00:52:53,560 --> 00:52:55,040
I don't think I am anymore.

569
00:53:03,160 --> 00:53:04,480
What are you doing now?

570
00:53:05,880 --> 00:53:07,360
Working on animation like you wanted?

571
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:13,880
Mm. I'm working and building my portfolio.

572
00:53:16,880 --> 00:53:17,880
What about you?

573
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:19,680
How have you been?

574
00:53:24,160 --> 00:53:25,160
Me?

575
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:28,680
Just living my life.

576
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:31,720
I moved back to Thailand
and opened a photo studio.

577
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:41,120
What about him?

578
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:43,120
Have you been together long?

579
00:53:45,280 --> 00:53:46,520
We've been dating for a while.

580
00:53:49,200 --> 00:53:50,200
Is he good to you?

581
00:53:51,320 --> 00:53:52,400
Or is he shitty like I was?

582
00:53:59,120 --> 00:54:00,120
I don't know.

583
00:54:02,120 --> 00:54:03,520
We'll have to see about that.

584
00:54:08,600 --> 00:54:10,920
But I don't think anyone
could treat me worse than you did.

585
00:54:22,040 --> 00:54:23,040
You know…

586
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:28,240
ever since we broke up,
I haven't been with anyone.

587
00:54:33,840 --> 00:54:34,840
That's good.

588
00:54:36,880 --> 00:54:39,320
It means you haven't left scars
on someone else's heart.

589
00:54:45,640 --> 00:54:47,280
I'm glad you're happy.

590
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:51,520
You might not believe me,

591
00:54:54,440 --> 00:54:56,360
but I've never loved anyone
the way I loved you.

592
00:55:01,800 --> 00:55:02,800
I missed you.

593
00:55:06,440 --> 00:55:07,440
Did you ever miss me?

594
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:17,200
I'm not answering that.

595
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:23,120
Can I hug you?

596
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:35,440
Let's not.

597
00:55:36,320 --> 00:55:38,000
I gave you everything I had back then.

598
00:55:52,320 --> 00:55:54,240
Nick, are you done?

599
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:55,920
Yeah.

600
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:58,560
You were taking a while,
so I came to get you.

601
00:55:59,240 --> 00:56:00,240
Let's go back inside.

602
00:56:00,840 --> 00:56:01,840
Mm.

603
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:03,720
Excuse us.

604
00:56:05,920 --> 00:56:06,920
I'm glad I saw you.

605
00:56:36,160 --> 00:56:37,600
You were great today, Dean.

606
00:56:38,920 --> 00:56:40,760
I've never seen you on stage before.

607
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:43,960
How did you remember all those lines?

608
00:56:44,520 --> 00:56:46,600
Especially that love confession scene.

609
00:56:47,240 --> 00:56:49,520
I teared up watching you.

610
00:56:59,560 --> 00:57:00,560
Dean.

611
00:57:03,080 --> 00:57:04,080
Yeah?

612
00:57:04,240 --> 00:57:05,240
What's wrong?

613
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:07,280
I guess I'm just tired.

614
00:57:07,480 --> 00:57:09,040
Today was a lot.

615
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:19,000
Is it about Jack?

616
00:57:23,760 --> 00:57:25,520
No. It's nothing.

617
00:57:26,720 --> 00:57:27,720
Let's just drink.

618
00:57:46,640 --> 00:57:47,840
You can tell me anything.

619
00:58:11,520 --> 00:58:12,560
I'm getting pretty tipsy.

620
00:58:13,280 --> 00:58:16,400
I think I'll take a shower and go to bed.

621
00:58:48,840 --> 00:58:49,840
What's up, Timmy?

622
00:58:50,320 --> 00:58:52,480
(Are you a friend of the phone's owner?)

623
00:58:52,720 --> 00:58:54,960
(He's been in an accident.)

624
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:07,400
Jack.

625
00:59:07,480 --> 00:59:08,320
What happened?

626
00:59:08,360 --> 00:59:10,000
The ride Timmy took home was in a crash.

627
00:59:10,320 --> 00:59:11,360
It's my fault.

628
00:59:11,720 --> 00:59:12,880
I asked him to drink with me.

629
00:59:15,600 --> 00:59:17,080
Jack, this isn't your fault.

630
00:59:17,360 --> 00:59:18,360
It's okay.

631
00:59:18,920 --> 00:59:20,400
Timmy's going to be fine.

632
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:25,400
I'm here.

633
00:59:26,440 --> 00:59:27,440
I'm right here.

634
00:59:52,440 --> 00:59:54,200
(Next Episode)
You guys are friends, after all.

635
00:59:54,200 --> 00:59:55,760
Patch things up.

636
00:59:55,840 --> 00:59:59,240
Let my near-death experience
count for something.

637
00:59:59,240 --> 01:00:01,080
So you're just gonna follow me around?

638
01:00:01,120 --> 01:00:02,040
Don't you have anything to do?

639
01:00:02,040 --> 01:00:03,216
Well, you wouldn't talk to me.

640
01:00:03,240 --> 01:00:04,320
You want to talk?

641
01:00:04,640 --> 01:00:05,080
Yes.
Prove it.

642
01:00:06,080 --> 01:00:07,080
Where are you going next?

643
01:00:07,360 --> 01:00:08,496
Want to grab something to eat?

644
01:00:08,520 --> 01:00:09,520
Let's not.

645
01:00:09,680 --> 01:00:11,160
Can I take care of you, Dean?

646
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:12,800
Will you give me that chance?

647
01:00:14,880 --> 01:00:16,680
Tua, I was wrong!

648
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:17,880
Will you please forgive me?

649
01:00:17,960 --> 01:00:20,280
Arnold, what are you doing?
